    en: "When an adult child has an intellectual or developmental disability and cannot manage their own affairs, a parent or other interested person may petition Surrogate's Court for legal guardianship under Surrogate's Court Procedure Act (SCPA) Article 17-A. The court-appointed guardian has authority to make personal, medical, and property decisions for the person. Courts now consider whether less restrictive alternatives — supported decision-making under Mental Hygiene Law 82 or a tailored Article 81 guardianship — fit the situation better than a broad 17-A appointment."
